thread.title_full: High School Sports Round-up: Mustangs score back to back Boy's Soccer Finger Lakes East wins

author: Gary Pinneo
title: High School Sports Round-up: Mustangs score back to back Boy's Soccer Finger Lakes East wins
text: Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 12:41 PM By Gary Pinneo Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 12:41 PM Penn Yan With the regular season schedule rapidly drawing to an end, the high flying Penn Yan Mustang boy's soccer team continues to roll league wins. The Orange and Blue crew recorded two more Finger Lakes East wins Tuesday and Thursday to improve their league mark to 9-3 and 11-5 overall with the Section V tournament looming on the horizon. Penn Yan 3 Midlakes 1 On Tuesday evening (10/13) in Penn Yan, the Mustangs downed Midlakes 3-1. Noah Hullings, Scott Fingar, and Gage Ponsetti scored goals for the scrappy Mustangs. This was Fingar's 16th goal of the season, the best on the team. Fingar also added an assist, as did teammate Noah Hullings. Jon McKay stopped 3 Screaming Eagle shots in goal for Penn Yan. Penn Yan 2 Newark 0 On Thursday afternoon, the Mustangs traveled to Newark to take on the Newark Reds. The red-hot Mustangs walked off with a 2-0 win over the host Reds in this contest. Once again, Noah Hullings and Scott Fingar provided the Orange and Blue offense, scoring a goal each. It was the 17th goal for Fingar. Tate Stewart added an assist on each of the Penn Yan goals. Jon McKay recorded the shutout win for the Mustangs making 9 saves in the nets. HAC 3 Marcus Whitman 0 The Marcus Whitman Wildcat boy's soccer team dropped games to two Finger Lakes West opponents. On Tuesday in Rushville, the wildcats were shutout by the Wolves of HAC 3-0. Tim Cornish picked up 6 save in goal for Whitman. South Seneca/Romulus 6 Marcus Whitman 0 On Thursday afternoon, the Wildcats were white-washed by South Seneca/Romulus 6-0. Tim Cornish recorded 7 saves in goal for the wildcats. With the losses, Marcus Whitman falls to 1-11 in the Finger Lakes West and 2-14 overall. Girlâ€™s Soccer Dundee 3 Romulus 0 The Dundee Scot girl's soccer team hosted Romulus in Dundee in a Finger Lakes West match. The hometown Scots shutout the Warriors from Romulus 3-0. Once again Dundee's talented scoring machine, Tayler Morrison accounted for all three Dundee tallies. Madison Hill added 2 assists while Emily Oughterson added 1 assist. Andi Wood stopped 4 Romulus shots in goal for Dundee. The Scots improved their Finger Lakes West record to 3-7 with the win. They are 5-9 overall. Marcus Whitman 5 Romulus 0 The Marcus Whitman girl's soccer team shutout Romulus 5-0 at home Thursday afternoon. Emily Thompson scored 4 goals to lead the Wildcat offense. Audrie Prusnowski added a goal and an assist. Michaela Commisso and Ellie Nemitz also picked up assists. Katrina Meyer and Ellie Nemita combined for 6 saves in the nets for Whitman. (3-8, 5-11). On Wednesday afternoon, Marcus Whitman was shutout by Waterloo in a non-league game played in Waterloo. Katrina Meyers recorded 11 saves in goal. for Marcus Whitman. Page 2 of 2 - Volleyball The Penn Yan Mustang girl's volleyball team continued to dominate opponents in Finger Lakes East action. The Orange and Blue net crew rolled over Geneva and Midlakes in Finger Lakes League games to improve their record to 8-2 in the league and 13-2 overall. Penn Yan 3 Geneva 1 On Tuesday afternoon in Penn Yan, the Mustangs defeated the Geneva Panther 3-1. For Penn Yan, Sydney Bloom recorded 5 kills and 18 digs while teammate Jessica Covell served 3 aces, added 2 kills and 16 digs. Also helping the Mustangs to the win was Jess Decker with 6 aces, 6 kills, and 3 digs. Kelly Bray added 15 assists, 9 digs, and 2 kills. Emily Wunder 14 kills , 17 digs, and 3 blocks while Brie Yonge contributed 10 digs and served 5 aces. Penn Yan 3 Midlakes 0 On Thursday, the high flying Mustangs hosted Midlakes. The Orange and Blue scored a 3-0 win in this contest. Kelly Bray dished out 15 assists and 6 digs, Brie Yonge 9 digs and 2 kills, Emily Wunder 9 digs, 5 kills, 5 aces, and 3 blocks. Teammate Jess Decker recorded 8 kills and 3 digs, Sydney bloom 4 kills and 2 aces, and Elissa Callaway served 3 aces and contributed 3 digs and 1 block. By Gary Pinneo
